ONLY OPEN AFTER SUNSET
1 PER PERSON. NO DELIVERIES

97
00:04:53.251 --> 00:04:54.961
<i>-One per person.</i>
<i>-I see.</i>

98
00:04:56.587 --> 00:04:58.589
<i>The welfare has improved significantly.</i>

99
00:05:00.508 --> 00:05:02.844
That's what they do at college retreats.

100
00:05:05.471 --> 00:05:06.931
Shall we go eat ice cream?

101
00:05:07.890 --> 00:05:08.766
With whom?

102
00:05:09.976 --> 00:05:11.311
-With whom?
-All three?

103
00:05:14.939 --> 00:05:18.026
I'll go and talk with I-geon this time.

104
00:05:18.526 --> 00:05:20.778
I'll go and talk with I-geon.

105
00:05:20.862 --> 00:05:22.196
-Go ahead.
-Okay.

106
00:05:22.280 --> 00:05:23.364
-Have fun.
-Okay.

107
00:05:29.162 --> 00:05:31.581
What did you talk about
for four whole hours?

108
00:05:31.664 --> 00:05:32.540
Four hours?

109
00:05:32.623 --> 00:05:34.083
-Yes.
-It wasn't four hours.

110
00:05:34.167 --> 00:05:35.376
-No way.
-What?

111
00:05:35.960 --> 00:05:37.628
I couldn't stand it any longer.

112
00:05:37.712 --> 00:05:40.340
And I had to… you know?

113
00:05:40.423 --> 00:05:44.218
-What?
-I ended up third-wheeling.

114
00:05:45.094 --> 00:05:46.345
Has it really been four hours?

115
00:05:47.013 --> 00:05:48.431
It wasn't really four hours.

116
00:05:50.725 --> 00:05:52.143
-Have you been there?
-Where?

117
00:05:52.226 --> 00:05:53.061
-There.
-There?

118
00:05:53.144 --> 00:05:55.104
-Yes.
-Yes. I have.

119
00:05:55.188 --> 00:05:56.355
I see.

120
00:05:56.439 --> 00:05:58.066
You've really been everywhere.

121
00:05:59.358 --> 00:06:00.276
Seriously.

122
00:06:01.944 --> 00:06:03.988
-This is driving me crazy.
-Why?

123
00:06:04.072 --> 00:06:06.991
-You've been everywhere.
-I haven't. I still have some places left.

124
00:06:07.075 --> 00:06:07.950
Which way is it?

125
00:06:09.660 --> 00:06:11.370
-We continue this way.
-Okay.

126
00:06:13.289 --> 00:06:14.707
This is how it looks.

127
00:06:15.416 --> 00:06:16.709
I've been here once.

128
00:06:17.835 --> 00:06:19.087
-To get water?
-Yes.

129
00:06:19.170 --> 00:06:22.590
-You've really been everywhere.
-Well. I had to get water.

130
00:06:25.802 --> 00:06:29.472
-It's only open after sunset?
-Yes. it has to be dark.

131
00:06:31.182 --> 00:06:33.267
I want this one.

132
00:06:33.351 --> 00:06:36.062
They've melted a bit.
We should eat them quickly.

133
00:06:44.529 --> 00:06:46.155
That looks so appetizing.

134
00:06:47.573 --> 00:06:49.158
-It's good.
-Yes.

135
00:06:55.331 --> 00:06:56.749
-Why am I like this?
-Get up.

136
00:06:57.291 --> 00:06:58.459
Just stand up and…

137
00:06:58.543 --> 00:07:00.002
Exactly.

138
00:07:03.381 --> 00:07:04.966
Seriously. why am I like this?

139
00:07:05.633 --> 00:07:07.468
I'm always like this.

140
00:07:07.552 --> 00:07:09.011
-You're always spilling?
-Yes.

141
00:07:12.807 --> 00:07:13.766
It's all dirty now.

142
00:07:14.350 --> 00:07:15.726
Should I pour water on it?

143
00:07:20.314 --> 00:07:21.232
I'll do it.

144
00:07:22.316 --> 00:07:23.443
Get up for a second.

145
00:07:32.243 --> 00:07:33.327
What was that?

146
00:07:41.294 --> 00:07:42.670
What are you doing?

147
00:07:47.925 --> 00:07:50.011
I end up laughing with them
for some reason.

148
00:07:50.094 --> 00:07:52.972
-We're in tune with their emotions.
-Yes.

149
00:07:53.055 --> 00:07:55.266
-Yes.
-It's stupidly funny.

150
00:07:55.349 --> 00:07:56.392
Right.

151
00:07:57.018 --> 00:07:58.895
What happened was…

152
00:07:58.978 --> 00:08:00.354
-Let me explain.
-Seriously.

153
00:08:00.438 --> 00:08:01.481
It didn't even…

154
00:08:04.066 --> 00:08:05.109
I'm nervous now.

155
00:08:05.651 --> 00:08:07.445
You weren't even close.

156
00:08:10.239 --> 00:08:11.365
That was hilarious.

157
00:08:13.868 --> 00:08:14.911
That was so funny.

158
00:08:17.455 --> 00:08:18.831
-Watch this.
-Okay.

159
00:08:23.669 --> 00:08:24.629
I did it.

160
00:08:33.429 --> 00:08:37.183
I wonder what you'd be like
as a boyfriend.

161
00:08:39.227 --> 00:08:40.311
-Me?
-Yes.

162
00:08:45.024 --> 00:08:47.401
What are you like as a girlfriend?

163
00:08:48.152 --> 00:08:51.989
I really hate it
when someone keeps doing what I dislike.

164
00:08:52.573 --> 00:08:53.741
Give me an example.

165
00:08:54.408 --> 00:08:57.245
I personally hate it
when someone says. "Hey. you."

166
00:08:57.328 --> 00:08:58.287
-"Hey. you"?
-Yes.

167
00:08:58.371 --> 00:09:01.999
So that's why
you asked me that in Paradise.

168
00:09:02.083 --> 00:09:03.167
Yes. that's right.

169
00:09:03.960 --> 00:09:04.794
DAY 4 PARADISE

170
00:09:04.877 --> 00:09:07.880
What about you? It's hard to ask
since I don't know the guys.

171
00:09:08.631 --> 00:09:09.465
My type…

172
00:09:10.716 --> 00:09:12.927
Is there anyone you're interested in?

173
00:09:13.511 --> 00:09:15.388
-Yes. there is.
-Really?

174
00:09:16.514 --> 00:09:19.058
You can try to guess who it is.

175
00:09:20.434 --> 00:09:21.811
I'll say. "Hey. is it him?"

176
00:09:24.897 --> 00:09:26.649
Do you call your girlfriend "Hey"?

177
00:09:27.275 --> 00:09:28.526
-To my girlfriend?
-Yes.

178
00:09:29.110 --> 00:09:29.986
Of course not.

179
00:09:32.947 --> 00:09:36.158
-I don't say "Hey."
-I see.

180
00:09:39.328 --> 00:09:41.539
But who addresses
their girlfriend as "Hey. you"?

181
00:09:41.622 --> 00:09:43.457
No one. but maybe during a fight?

182
00:09:43.541 --> 00:09:44.625
-Then I…
-When they're mad?

183
00:09:44.709 --> 00:09:46.127
-I can't.
-Right.

184
00:09:46.210 --> 00:09:49.797
I feel like you'd say "Hey. you"
to your girlfriend during an argument.

185
00:09:52.425 --> 00:09:53.467
Honestly?

186
00:09:54.010 --> 00:09:56.012
-Yes.
-I'll think about it.

187
00:09:56.095 --> 00:09:57.054
During a fight…

188
00:09:58.264 --> 00:10:03.644
I'm not sure if I'm distorting my memory.
but I don't remember saying "Hey."

189
00:10:03.728 --> 00:10:05.187
But I've used "you" before.

190
00:10:05.271 --> 00:10:06.397
That's not too bad.

191
00:10:06.981 --> 00:10:09.567
I think I've said.
"You said this" or "You did this."

192
00:10:10.526 --> 00:10:11.527
That's not bad.

193
00:10:20.995 --> 00:10:21.954
That's not too bad.

194
00:10:23.039 --> 00:10:24.832
What are you like during a fight?

195
00:10:25.833 --> 00:10:27.043
-During a fight?
-Yes.

196
00:10:27.126 --> 00:10:29.629
I wonder what you're like when you're mad.

197
00:10:29.712 --> 00:10:31.422
I don't bring it up right away.

198
00:10:31.922 --> 00:10:33.090
-I think about it first.
-Why?

199
00:10:34.175 --> 00:10:36.052
Because I could be mistaken.

200
00:10:36.135 --> 00:10:37.511
-I could've misunderstood.
-I see.

201
00:10:37.595 --> 00:10:38.929
I know what you mean.

202
00:10:39.013 --> 00:10:41.974
I think about it at night and sleep on it.

203
00:10:42.058 --> 00:10:44.226
-If I feel the same. then I act on it.
-Right.

204
00:10:44.310 --> 00:10:47.146
-But I usually don't feel the same way.
-Right.

205
00:10:47.229 --> 00:10:50.358
I'm a completely different person
during the day and at night.

206
00:10:50.441 --> 00:10:51.275
Right.

207
00:10:54.779 --> 00:10:56.530
It's fun talking to you.

208
00:11:03.704 --> 00:11:05.539
Then you should've come down sooner.

209
00:11:07.917 --> 00:11:08.751
Right?

210
00:11:11.128 --> 00:11:12.296
Seriously.

211
00:11:18.427 --> 00:11:19.762
-This energy feels right.
-Yes.

212
00:11:19.845 --> 00:11:22.348
-She's so different.
-Totally different.

213
00:11:23.432 --> 00:11:24.934
You were so funny.

214
00:11:25.017 --> 00:11:25.893
Why?

215
00:11:25.976 --> 00:11:28.312
It was so funny
watching you pour the water.

216
00:11:29.563 --> 00:11:32.191
I made a fool of myself.

217
00:11:32.274 --> 00:11:33.109
Seriously.

218
00:11:34.485 --> 00:11:35.945
-I was going to do it.
-"I'll do it."

219
00:11:36.028 --> 00:11:38.030
But you insisted on doing it.

220
00:11:41.409 --> 00:11:42.326
You're funny.

221
00:11:42.868 --> 00:11:43.828
You're a funny guy.

222
00:11:44.662 --> 00:11:47.123
And I think
you're good at holding conversations.

223
00:11:48.124 --> 00:11:50.960
-I think so too.
-I see.

224
00:11:53.295 --> 00:11:54.880
When you listen to them.

225
00:11:54.964 --> 00:11:58.801
they usually talk about
things that really matter.

226
00:11:58.884 --> 00:12:00.511
-Especially as couples.
-True.

227
00:12:00.594 --> 00:12:03.180
-But it's never like that with Sung-min.
-Right.

228
00:12:03.264 --> 00:12:05.099
The first Paradise trip must be special.

229
00:12:05.182 --> 00:12:07.560
-It's like their first love.
-Like a first love?

230
00:12:07.643 --> 00:12:10.479
Not only did Mina Sue say so
but Go-eun feels that way. too.

231
00:12:10.563 --> 00:12:12.440
Since her first trip to Paradise
was with him?

232
00:12:12.523 --> 00:12:16.152
Yes. "I think Sung-min means a lot to me."

233
00:12:16.235 --> 00:12:17.570
That may be what she's feeling.

234
00:12:18.154 --> 00:12:20.406
Anyway. in our eyes.
she seems to like I-geon.

235
00:12:20.489 --> 00:12:21.824
It looks like it. right?

236
00:12:21.907 --> 00:12:22.741
-Yes.
-Yes.

237
00:12:22.825 --> 00:12:25.828
-But who knows if she feels the same way?
-I wouldn't know.

238
00:12:26.579 --> 00:12:28.664
-Can we come in?
-Sure.

239
00:12:28.747 --> 00:12:29.790
It's a humble place.

240
00:12:30.458 --> 00:12:31.667
Where is Sung-hun's bed?

241
00:12:32.418 --> 00:12:33.252
Sam?

242
00:12:33.335 --> 00:12:34.336
-Here.
-Here?

243
00:12:34.837 --> 00:12:36.630
Right. I saw him reading here.

244
00:12:36.714 --> 00:12:37.923
It's cold.

245
00:12:39.258 --> 00:12:41.969
What are you doing?
What was that just now?

246
00:12:42.595 --> 00:12:44.847
What is up with you? That hurts.

247
00:12:45.973 --> 00:12:47.475
What's wrong with her?

248
00:12:56.650 --> 00:12:59.570
Wow. he reads this for fun? Is he crazy?

249
00:13:03.741 --> 00:13:07.244
-What are you doing?
-I'm so curious. really.

250
00:13:07.328 --> 00:13:10.331
I'm curious.
but Hee-sun will get to know first.

251
00:13:11.165 --> 00:13:12.374
Excuse me.

252
00:13:14.543 --> 00:13:17.296
Why today of all days?

253
00:13:17.379 --> 00:13:19.798
If I hadn't lost…

254
00:13:20.424 --> 00:13:22.801
If I had gotten third place…
No. never mind.

255
00:13:22.885 --> 00:13:24.762
-I had to get second place. right?
-Yes.

256
00:13:25.262 --> 00:13:27.765
Maybe you'll get a chance to go next time.

257
00:13:27.848 --> 00:13:29.725
But the first trip is significant.

258
00:13:29.808 --> 00:13:31.477
You wanted to go on his first trip.

259
00:13:31.560 --> 00:13:32.978
It's like the first…

260
00:13:33.771 --> 00:13:35.439
-The first Paradise trip?
-Yes.

261
00:13:35.523 --> 00:13:37.566
-I wanted it to be with me.
-I see.

262
00:13:37.650 --> 00:13:43.155
But when Hee-sun returns.
she'll know more about him than I do.

263
00:13:44.740 --> 00:13:45.658
Before me.

264
00:13:46.325 --> 00:13:48.577
So I'm a bit disappointed.

265
00:13:48.661 --> 00:13:51.997
But don't you think
Sung-hun's feelings are steadfast?

266
00:13:52.081 --> 00:13:54.708
That's what he said.
but what if they aren't?

267
00:13:55.292 --> 00:13:58.420
But Sam. in his own way…

268
00:13:59.046 --> 00:14:00.548
-He has his own standard?
-He's solid.

269
00:14:00.631 --> 00:14:03.259
Everyone says
you have nothing to worry about.

270
00:14:03.842 --> 00:14:05.469
Have some faith in him.

271
00:14:09.139 --> 00:14:13.936
Why is Mina Sue always uninterested
when the person is right next to her

272
00:14:14.019 --> 00:14:16.272
and then starts pursuing them too late?

273
00:14:16.355 --> 00:14:18.315
-It's such a shame.
-Yes. it really is.

274
00:14:18.399 --> 00:14:21.360
What can you do in his bed
when he's in another bed now?

275
00:14:22.903 --> 00:14:23.821
He's in Paradise.

276
00:14:23.904 --> 00:14:24.989
What do you mean?

277
00:14:25.072 --> 00:14:26.031
Not like that…

278
00:14:27.116 --> 00:14:30.995
-She only notices them once they're gone.
-Right.

279
00:14:32.204 --> 00:14:33.622
{\an8}PARADISE
PARK HEE-SUN & LEE SUNG-HUN

280
00:14:33.706 --> 00:14:34.540
{\an8}Let's go.

281
00:14:36.750 --> 00:14:37.668
It's warm. right?

282
00:14:38.919 --> 00:14:39.837
It's so warm.

283
00:14:41.630 --> 00:14:42.756
I love it.

284
00:14:53.934 --> 00:14:55.519
-Is it good?
-It's so good.

285
00:14:56.896 --> 00:14:58.105
What is your love language?

286
00:15:00.566 --> 00:15:04.570
-When do you feel the most loved?
-I like being taken care of.

287
00:15:07.031 --> 00:15:09.199
-Why is it great?
-I like taking care of people.

288
00:15:09.283 --> 00:15:10.826
-Really?
-Yes. the acts of service.

289
00:15:13.203 --> 00:15:14.580
Why didn't you take care of me?

290
00:15:17.207 --> 00:15:18.042
In Inferno?

291
00:15:19.627 --> 00:15:22.046
How could I when you had someone else?

292
00:15:25.382 --> 00:15:28.093
How do you express your love?

293
00:15:29.136 --> 00:15:30.304
-How do I give love?
-Yes.

294
00:15:30.387 --> 00:15:32.306
I like giving gifts.

295
00:15:34.725 --> 00:15:36.143
You and I are quite similar.

296
00:15:36.685 --> 00:15:39.605
Yeah. I like traveling together too.

297
00:15:42.107 --> 00:15:45.527
-We're compatible on realistic things.
-Yes.

298
00:15:45.611 --> 00:15:48.697
-I like going on vacations and trips.
-I see.

299
00:15:50.366 --> 00:15:52.743
Do you like spending time
with your partner?

300
00:15:55.037 --> 00:15:56.997
Most of my relationships
have been long-distance.

301
00:15:57.081 --> 00:15:58.666
-I see.
-I didn't get to see them often.

302
00:15:58.749 --> 00:16:01.794
I like seeing my partners every day.

303
00:16:01.877 --> 00:16:03.879
Well. New York is pretty close by.

304
00:16:05.339 --> 00:16:08.258
-Everything's close to New York.
-True.

305
00:16:10.052 --> 00:16:13.555
After getting to know you better.
I'm still fascinated.

306
00:16:15.265 --> 00:16:16.141
Seriously.

307
00:16:18.102 --> 00:16:20.104
I think we'd get along well.

308
00:16:20.187 --> 00:16:21.897
-In the real world.
-I see.

309
00:16:21.981 --> 00:16:24.066
I think about that stuff a lot.

310
00:16:24.149 --> 00:16:27.236
-Like how things will be after all this.
-After?

311
00:16:28.153 --> 00:16:30.864
Who can I realistically
have a relationship with?

312
00:16:31.907 --> 00:16:34.660
I think realistically.
we'd be a good match.

313
00:16:37.371 --> 00:16:38.414
You two should date.

314
00:16:39.415 --> 00:16:41.542
-They're compatible.
-They look great together.

315
00:16:42.292 --> 00:16:45.295
After seven days.
this feels like my life now.

316
00:16:45.379 --> 00:16:46.463
Right.

317
00:16:46.547 --> 00:16:48.507
-Everyone's so immersed.
-Exactly.

318
00:16:48.590 --> 00:16:52.428
My life now is just waking up
and going out to talk right away.

319
00:16:52.511 --> 00:16:53.345
"Let's talk."

320
00:16:53.429 --> 00:16:55.139
"I haven't had breakfast. but let's talk."

321
00:16:55.222 --> 00:16:57.057
Why didn't you ask me?

322
00:16:57.141 --> 00:16:59.852
I haven't talked to a lot of people.

323
00:16:59.935 --> 00:17:02.021
Have you talked a lot with Mina Sue?

324
00:17:02.855 --> 00:17:04.106
Yes. I think so.

325
00:17:04.940 --> 00:17:09.069
But I find it hard
to understand her and what she's feeling.

326
00:17:09.153 --> 00:17:11.864
-I'm sure she'll figure it out.
-On her own.

327
00:17:12.531 --> 00:17:13.741
Love is self-serve.

328
00:17:13.824 --> 00:17:15.451
-Right.
-Love is self-serve.

329
00:17:16.493 --> 00:17:18.746
-I should focus on myself.
-Exactly.

330
00:17:19.830 --> 00:17:21.040
But from now on…

331
00:17:25.294 --> 00:17:28.130
-I'll talk to you more tomorrow.
-Sounds good.

332
00:17:28.213 --> 00:17:29.631
And the day after that. too.

333
00:17:44.730 --> 00:17:47.900
-I think he'll have second thoughts.
-It works because they're both in America.

334
00:17:47.983 --> 00:17:49.777
-It seems likely.
-Yes.

335
00:17:49.860 --> 00:17:52.780
-The mood here is really heated.
-Really.

336
00:17:52.863 --> 00:17:55.032
-It's such a realistic conversation.
-Right.

337
00:17:55.115 --> 00:17:57.618
They can meet in America.
and Sung-hun has to go back.

338
00:17:57.701 --> 00:17:58.535
-Yes.
-Right.

339
00:17:58.619 --> 00:18:01.538
So this is quite significant
and can't be overlooked.

340
00:18:01.622 --> 00:18:04.041
Someone who checks all the boxes
came into play.

341
00:18:04.124 --> 00:18:04.958
Exactly.

342
00:18:05.042 --> 00:18:07.127
And it wasn't just one-sided.

343
00:18:07.211 --> 00:18:09.088
-Hee-sun was very flirty too.
-Yes.

344
00:18:09.171 --> 00:18:11.048
-She said. "Why didn't you ask me?"
-Right.

345
00:18:11.131 --> 00:18:14.009
-I think Hee-sun is wavering a lot.
-I see.

346
00:18:14.093 --> 00:18:15.511
They get along well.

347
00:18:15.594 --> 00:18:19.473
But of all people. it had to be
those intertwined with Mina Sue.

348
00:18:19.556 --> 00:18:21.642
Sung-hun and Hee-sun.

349
00:18:21.725 --> 00:18:24.311
-Right.
-If they actually get together.

350
00:18:24.394 --> 00:18:28.148
I really think
Mina Sue might end up alone.

351
00:18:28.232 --> 00:18:32.444
She might end up with nothing
but a coming-of-age moment.

352
00:18:32.528 --> 00:18:34.238
Something's happening.

353
00:18:35.114 --> 00:18:36.490
Mina Sue is in trouble.

354
00:18:37.157 --> 00:18:38.784
PARADISE
LEE JOO-YOUNG & KIM JAE-JIN

355
00:18:38.867 --> 00:18:39.785
Here we are.

356
00:18:41.286 --> 00:18:42.830
Now that I've washed up. I feel great.

357
00:18:44.414 --> 00:18:45.791
Do you want anything?

358
00:18:45.874 --> 00:18:48.794
-I want some. Can you pour me a glass?
-Of course.

359
00:18:51.171 --> 00:18:53.340
Today. it's about whatever you want.

360
00:18:54.091 --> 00:18:55.467
Whatever you want.

361
00:18:55.551 --> 00:18:57.761
-This is all I ever wanted.
-This is it.

362
00:18:57.845 --> 00:18:59.096
I found my spot.

363
00:18:59.179 --> 00:19:03.016
Since you're the queen today.
I'll give you whatever you ask for.

364
00:19:03.100 --> 00:19:03.934
Okay.

365
00:19:04.643 --> 00:19:06.478
-A bite of cheesecake. please.
-Okay.

366
00:19:11.066 --> 00:19:12.901
-A bite of cheesecake.
-Here you go.

367
00:19:20.200 --> 00:19:21.201
What would you like?

368
00:19:22.661 --> 00:19:23.871
-Cheesecake?
-Cheesecake.

369
00:19:26.957 --> 00:19:28.750
Yes. you should be able to finish this.

370
00:19:32.963 --> 00:19:35.883
I feel like I'll remember this cheesecake
even after we leave.

371
00:19:37.676 --> 00:19:38.844
-I love it.
-Yes.

372
00:19:44.850 --> 00:19:46.310
-Is that something else?
-Yes.

373
00:19:54.318 --> 00:19:55.944
-You're tired. aren't you?
-No.

374
00:19:56.028 --> 00:19:58.197
-You have sleepy eyes.
-Yes. I'm tired.

375
00:20:00.324 --> 00:20:01.325
Go brush your teeth.

376
00:20:01.408 --> 00:20:02.951
-Do you want to brush your teeth?
-Yes.

377
00:20:04.870 --> 00:20:06.038
Go brush your teeth.

378
00:20:08.790 --> 00:20:10.500
I wish someone else would do it for me.

379
00:20:13.378 --> 00:20:14.338
I'll do it for you.

380
00:20:37.611 --> 00:20:38.445
Gosh.

381
00:20:39.655 --> 00:20:40.948
What's with that look?

382
00:20:45.744 --> 00:20:47.204
I should go brush my teeth.

383
00:20:49.706 --> 00:20:50.540
Go ahead.

384
00:20:51.083 --> 00:20:52.793
Should I change into pajamas?

385
00:20:53.669 --> 00:20:54.544
You brought pajamas?

386
00:21:04.930 --> 00:21:06.098
After I wash up.

387
00:21:06.181 --> 00:21:08.642
-let's go for a walk.
-Okay.

388
00:21:09.851 --> 00:21:12.437
But we can sleep if you're tired.
You should sleep well.

389
00:21:12.521 --> 00:21:13.605
-Really?
-Yes.

390
00:21:13.689 --> 00:21:15.440
Who knows what will happen tomorrow?

391
00:21:31.999 --> 00:21:33.917
-Good night.
-Good night.

392
00:21:37.504 --> 00:21:40.966
I hate finding myself grinning
while watching them.

393
00:21:42.551 --> 00:21:43.719
I was smiling too.

394
00:21:43.802 --> 00:21:44.678
You can't help it.

395
00:21:44.761 --> 00:21:46.888
-You just can't stop smiling.
-I don't want to smile.

396
00:21:46.972 --> 00:21:50.142
-I'm sure everyone was.
-Why am I grinning like a fool?

397
00:21:50.225 --> 00:21:51.518
I should zip my lips.

398
00:21:55.522 --> 00:21:59.192
{\an8}PARADISE
KIM MIN-GEE & LIM SU-BEEN

399
00:22:00.694 --> 00:22:02.738
-Are those your pajamas?
-Yes.

400
00:22:04.573 --> 00:22:05.574
They're my pajamas.

401
00:22:05.657 --> 00:22:06.992
-They suit you.
-Thank you.

402
00:22:07.075 --> 00:22:08.076
They were a gift.

403
00:22:15.042 --> 00:22:16.376
Do you want to sleep here?

404
00:22:17.878 --> 00:22:19.046
Don't make me laugh.

405
00:22:19.129 --> 00:22:22.049
Wait. I'm the one who said it.
I'll stop joking around.

406
00:22:22.883 --> 00:22:24.468
-I'll lie down for a bit.
-Okay.

407
00:22:25.552 --> 00:22:27.512
We can just lie down
and drift off while talking.

408
00:22:27.596 --> 00:22:30.557
-I like falling asleep while talking.
-Right.

409
00:22:32.476 --> 00:22:34.603
You must be enjoying your time with me.

410
00:22:35.479 --> 00:22:38.023
-I really am.
-That's a relief.

411
00:22:38.106 --> 00:22:39.858
-Yes.
-This is fun.

412
00:22:41.401 --> 00:22:44.654
If we get the chance.
I think we should talk more.

413
00:22:45.781 --> 00:22:47.240
-Really?
-Like…

414
00:22:47.324 --> 00:22:48.366
You and I

415
00:22:48.992 --> 00:22:54.122
get along so well
that I want to keep on talking with you.

416
00:22:54.206 --> 00:22:55.040
Right.

417
00:22:55.123 --> 00:22:59.920
It's the first time I've felt like
there's not enough time.

418
00:23:00.962 --> 00:23:03.673
I wish we had more time.
I wish we had come earlier.

419
00:23:03.757 --> 00:23:06.259
-Had more time in Paradise.
-It does feel like we came later.

420
00:23:06.343 --> 00:23:07.385
Yes. we did.

421
00:23:07.469 --> 00:23:09.054
-Yes.
-We came much later.

422
00:23:09.137 --> 00:23:12.140
I'm glad we're here.
We finally got to know each other.

423
00:23:13.183 --> 00:23:14.976
Really.

424
00:23:15.060 --> 00:23:16.561
Like. how did we end up here?

425
00:23:17.104 --> 00:23:19.940
This isn't somewhere I can come
just because I want to.

426
00:23:20.023 --> 00:23:23.443
-Right.
-But we're here because I wanted to.

427
00:23:28.657 --> 00:23:29.783
Are you laughing?

428
00:23:30.909 --> 00:23:34.162
-I'm just feeling giddy.
-Right.

429
00:23:35.789 --> 00:23:40.627
I had a fixed image of you
from the moment I first met you.

430
00:23:40.710 --> 00:23:41.628
Right.

431
00:23:42.337 --> 00:23:43.463
But…

432
00:23:43.547 --> 00:23:46.842
I don't know how this will sound.
but you have a cute vibe.

433
00:23:48.260 --> 00:23:49.928
I see.

434
00:23:50.595 --> 00:23:51.721
But I'm cuter.

435
00:23:53.306 --> 00:23:55.392
I'm even cuter than I am right now.

436
00:23:55.976 --> 00:23:58.270
I haven't shown you my cute side yet.

437
00:24:00.063 --> 00:24:01.439
-I see.
-Yes.

438
00:24:13.451 --> 00:24:15.829
-There's something going on here. too.
-There is.

439
00:24:15.912 --> 00:24:19.249
-Min-gee here seems so unfamiliar.
-Right?

440
00:24:19.332 --> 00:24:21.585
To us. she seemed to stand firm.

441
00:24:21.668 --> 00:24:25.046
having eyes for only one person.

442
00:24:25.130 --> 00:24:28.300
But Min-gee also has a fickle heart.

443
00:24:28.383 --> 00:24:32.554
Something must have taken over her
after her talk with Mina Sue.

444
00:24:33.388 --> 00:24:34.890
-An evil spirit.
-It took over.

445
00:24:34.973 --> 00:24:36.266
-Really.
-The spirit has moved.

446
00:24:36.349 --> 00:24:37.309
-Right.
-Really.

447
00:24:37.392 --> 00:24:39.686
-The spirit went to her.
-It's like they've switched.

448
00:24:39.769 --> 00:24:41.104
I can't believe you guys.

449
00:24:42.856 --> 00:24:43.899
But in a way…

450
00:24:43.982 --> 00:24:46.276
It does make sense in a way.

451
00:24:46.359 --> 00:24:47.944
-She wasn't like this.
-Right.

452
00:24:48.028 --> 00:24:50.405
-They're both acting so differently now.
-Yes.

453
00:24:50.488 --> 00:24:51.698
I can't get used to them.

454
00:24:51.781 --> 00:24:53.950
-She's acting so cute now.
-Yes.

455
00:24:59.831 --> 00:25:00.665
{\an8}Get up.

456
00:25:01.166 --> 00:25:02.667
{\an8}Why are you up so early?

457
00:25:02.751 --> 00:25:04.127
Wow. I'm so hungover.

458
00:25:05.003 --> 00:25:08.632
I feel terrible the morning
after drinking. I'm burning up.

459
00:25:08.715 --> 00:25:10.258
-She must've drunk a lot.
-Yes.

460
00:25:10.342 --> 00:25:12.761
-She drank enough to have a hangover.
-Yes.

461
00:25:13.887 --> 00:25:15.513
Did we sleep in the same bed last night?

462
00:25:16.556 --> 00:25:17.599
You don't remember?

463
00:25:17.682 --> 00:25:19.768
-Did we drink a lot?
-I guess so?

464
00:25:19.851 --> 00:25:21.436
He doesn't even remember?

465
00:25:22.062 --> 00:25:24.064
-Did I sleep here?
-Yes.

466
00:25:26.316 --> 00:25:27.234
So…

467
00:25:28.443 --> 00:25:29.903
-Why'd you sleep there?
-What?

468
00:25:29.986 --> 00:25:31.112
Why'd you sleep next to me?

469
00:25:31.196 --> 00:25:32.030
LAST NIGHT

470
00:25:32.113 --> 00:25:34.491
<i>-He slept there.</i>
<i>-They must've shared the bed.</i>

471
00:25:37.452 --> 00:25:39.037
<i>Oh. he got up.</i>

472
00:25:40.580 --> 00:25:41.790
<i>He must've got into bed.</i>

473
00:25:44.000 --> 00:25:46.002
{\an8}Normally. I would just sleep…

474
00:25:48.588 --> 00:25:50.090
{\an8}But it's so cold.

475
00:25:51.299 --> 00:25:52.842
{\an8}Min-gee. can I join you?

476
00:25:54.803 --> 00:25:55.762
Sure.

477
00:25:56.346 --> 00:25:58.890
<i>-He was just sleepy.</i>
<i>-He was cold.</i>

478
00:26:14.698 --> 00:26:18.368
<i>-I think he just really needed a blanket.</i>
<i>-Yes. he's pulling the blanket out.</i>

479
00:26:19.244 --> 00:26:22.080
Su-been had no ulterior motive.
He was just really cold.

480
00:26:34.384 --> 00:26:36.261
They only shared a bed

481
00:26:36.344 --> 00:26:39.764
because they had some drinks.
and he was cold.

482
00:26:40.432 --> 00:26:42.600
-He just needed a blanket.
-They just slept.

483
00:26:42.684 --> 00:26:44.978
-Right.
-For the sake of sleep.

484
00:26:46.938 --> 00:26:47.814
Are you laughing?

485
00:26:51.234 --> 00:26:53.111
Aren't you too comfortable around me?

486
00:26:53.194 --> 00:26:54.279
It's not like that.

487
00:26:58.033 --> 00:27:02.954
{\an8}INFERNO

488
00:27:33.401 --> 00:27:35.779
-Is this the only place to work out?
-Yes. this is it.

489
00:27:36.363 --> 00:27:37.572
They're talking again.

490
00:27:38.865 --> 00:27:40.075
He's really something.

491
00:27:40.617 --> 00:27:41.493
Wow. seriously.

492
00:27:42.118 --> 00:27:42.994
He's her shadow.

493
00:27:44.412 --> 00:27:47.082
I get that he's persistent. but this is…

494
00:27:48.291 --> 00:27:49.334
It's so early.

495
00:27:49.417 --> 00:27:50.710
-From the crack of dawn.
-Really.

496
00:27:51.669 --> 00:27:54.047
What's your workout routine.
Mr. Paper Doll?

497
00:27:54.130 --> 00:27:55.256
All of them.

498
00:27:55.340 --> 00:27:56.716
I can lift weights. too.

499
00:27:57.759 --> 00:27:58.593
Oh. really?

500
00:27:59.177 --> 00:28:00.428
I can't picture it.

501
00:28:00.512 --> 00:28:01.596
-Really?
-Yes.

502
00:28:02.180 --> 00:28:03.264
I can lift that much.

503
00:28:05.141 --> 00:28:07.811
-I step up when needed.
-I see.

504
00:28:17.862 --> 00:28:18.822
Is your face puffy?

505
00:28:20.156 --> 00:28:21.241
Don't look closely.

506
00:28:21.825 --> 00:28:24.202
-Or is it not?
-I think I'm a little puffy.

507
00:28:25.662 --> 00:28:27.288
You do look a bit puffy.

508
00:28:29.290 --> 00:28:30.625
-What?
-You're a bit puffy.

509
00:28:30.708 --> 00:28:33.044
-I am?
-Yes. your cheeks look fuller.

510
00:28:33.128 --> 00:28:34.295
Oh no.

511
00:28:35.255 --> 00:28:37.715
I'm sure the swelling
will go down as we walk.

512
00:28:43.054 --> 00:28:45.515
<i>Go-eun and Sung-min were taking a walk.</i>

513
00:28:46.266 --> 00:28:48.727
They even passed by me
while I was working out.

514
00:28:49.227 --> 00:28:53.440
Seeing them together made me so angry
that I ended up overdoing my workout.

515
00:29:04.743 --> 00:29:05.869
Darn it.

516
00:29:21.926 --> 00:29:25.930
-I'd be annoyed too if I were him.
-Yes.

517
00:29:26.014 --> 00:29:27.056
-Of course.
-Yes.

518
00:29:27.140 --> 00:29:29.517
Couldn't they have at least greeted him
as they passed?

519
00:29:29.601 --> 00:29:31.770
It could make him more determined.

520
00:29:31.853 --> 00:29:33.980
True. it's a natural motivation booster.

521
00:29:35.148 --> 00:29:37.233
-The sun isn't out--
-How is it?

522
00:29:37.317 --> 00:29:40.028
-How's what?
-How is the early morning in Inferno?

523
00:29:40.111 --> 00:29:41.112
It's nice.

524
00:29:41.196 --> 00:29:42.155
-Right?
-Yes.

525
00:29:43.656 --> 00:29:47.994
The first time
you went to Paradise with Min-gee…

526
00:29:48.953 --> 00:29:50.163
-Are you curious?
-Yes.

527
00:29:50.246 --> 00:29:53.917
According to Min-gee. our trip to Paradise
wasn't heart-fluttering at all.

528
00:29:54.584 --> 00:29:55.794
-Really?
-Yes.

529
00:29:56.628 --> 00:30:00.882
But honestly. I felt the same way.
It didn't get my heart racing.

530
00:30:00.965 --> 00:30:04.469
-I see.
-It felt different when I went with you.

531
00:30:04.969 --> 00:30:09.349
What was it like with me?
How did you feel?

532
00:30:09.432 --> 00:30:11.643
Talking with you…

533
00:30:11.726 --> 00:30:14.437
I always thought I was more of a listener.

534
00:30:14.521 --> 00:30:15.522
-I see.
-Yes.

535
00:30:15.605 --> 00:30:18.942
-But with you. I really opened up.
-Yes.

536
00:30:19.025 --> 00:30:22.195
-I end up talking about myself.
-Right.

537
00:30:22.779 --> 00:30:27.116
-When I realized how chatty I was…
-I see.

538
00:30:27.200 --> 00:30:29.160
I really liked that side of me.

539
00:30:31.746 --> 00:30:33.581
I've liked you since the moment we met.

540
00:30:34.082 --> 00:30:36.668
but after getting to know you.
I like you even more.

541
00:30:36.751 --> 00:30:38.169
-I see.
-Yeah.

542
00:30:38.837 --> 00:30:41.214
I think that's when I came to my decision.

543
00:30:41.297 --> 00:30:44.509
-You've been my top pick ever since.
-I see.

544
00:30:45.969 --> 00:30:50.014
There really must be something
about Sung-min that I don't see.

545
00:30:50.098 --> 00:30:52.058
-Really.
-There must be…

546
00:30:52.141 --> 00:30:54.143
-Right.
-Or is it because

547
00:30:54.227 --> 00:30:55.854
he speaks so politely?

548
00:30:55.937 --> 00:31:00.191
For example. he calls her by name
instead of saying "you."

549
00:31:00.275 --> 00:31:02.193
I wonder if that's what attracts her.

550
00:31:02.777 --> 00:31:06.281
Let's try to guess
whether Go-eun's heart leans more

551
00:31:06.948 --> 00:31:08.449
towards I-geon or Sung-min.

552
00:31:09.200 --> 00:31:13.288
I think her feelings are about
80% for I-geon and 20% for Sung-min.

553
00:31:13.371 --> 00:31:15.164
-That's a big difference.
-Yes.

554
00:31:15.248 --> 00:31:16.666
I think it's 60 to 40.

555
00:31:16.749 --> 00:31:19.419
She's split 60% for Sung-min
and 40% for I-geon.

556
00:31:19.502 --> 00:31:21.045
Here's why I think that.

557
00:31:21.129 --> 00:31:25.300
I wouldn't be able to sit through
such a long. boring conversation.

558
00:31:25.383 --> 00:31:30.346
You can't spend all day listening
to someone if you don't like the person.

559
00:31:30.430 --> 00:31:32.223
-Right.
-It would be so hard.

560
00:31:32.307 --> 00:31:35.101
-Right.
-Based on that alone. she does like him.

561
00:31:35.184 --> 00:31:38.104
-I think they talk for five hours a day.
-Seriously.

562
00:31:38.187 --> 00:31:40.231
There's no way she doesn't like him.

563
00:31:40.315 --> 00:31:44.485
Go-eun seems to prefer

564
00:31:44.569 --> 00:31:48.072
a relaxed. easygoing relationship
with chats like these

565
00:31:48.156 --> 00:31:50.116
over one that is more thrilling.

566
00:31:50.199 --> 00:31:52.744
That could be the case.

567
00:31:54.120 --> 00:31:55.163
I don't know.

568
00:32:01.794 --> 00:32:05.632
-Did you get to do everything you wanted?
-Yes. I did everything.

569
00:32:06.633 --> 00:32:08.843
I want to go to Paradise today. too.

570
00:32:08.927 --> 00:32:10.261
-Really?
-Yes.

571
00:32:12.263 --> 00:32:13.765
-I'll try.
-Please try.

572
00:32:16.684 --> 00:32:17.518
They're coming.

573
00:32:17.602 --> 00:32:18.603
-They're back.
-Stop.

574
00:32:18.686 --> 00:32:19.771
No way. Don't lie.

575
00:32:19.854 --> 00:32:20.772
-Really?
-Yes.

576
00:32:20.855 --> 00:32:23.316
-But there are only two couples.
-What's going on?

577
00:32:24.233 --> 00:32:26.694
-Joo-young and Jae-jin…
-They're behind them.

578
00:32:39.540 --> 00:32:41.376
Why wear sunglasses on a cloudy day?

579
00:32:47.006 --> 00:32:48.633
Mina Sue.

580
00:32:48.716 --> 00:32:50.593
-Hey.
-You're back.

581
00:32:51.886 --> 00:32:53.137
-Hey.
-Welcome back.

582
00:32:53.221 --> 00:32:54.973
-Hello.
-Hello.

583
00:32:57.684 --> 00:32:59.060
Did you have a nice time?

584
00:33:00.144 --> 00:33:01.562
Hi. all.

585
00:33:02.647 --> 00:33:03.982
-You're back.
-Yes.

586
00:33:13.783 --> 00:33:16.160
Welcome back.
Did you eat lots of good food?

587
00:33:16.703 --> 00:33:18.121
-Yes. I did.
-You did?

588
00:33:19.247 --> 00:33:21.082
-Wow. what is this?
-My slippers?

589
00:33:21.165 --> 00:33:22.834
Wow. your shoes are so cute.

590
00:33:24.168 --> 00:33:26.671
My goodness. They're so cute.

591
00:33:34.929 --> 00:33:37.056
She must feel awkward
for enjoying it too much.

592
00:33:37.557 --> 00:33:38.433
Right?

593
00:33:38.516 --> 00:33:40.727
-Is that what she's feeling?
-I see.

594
00:33:40.810 --> 00:33:44.897
-She's acting a bit awkward right now.
-Oh. you're right.

595
00:33:45.565 --> 00:33:46.733
Was it fun?

596
00:33:48.401 --> 00:33:50.820
I'm curious about
Sung-hun's first trip to Paradise.

597
00:33:50.903 --> 00:33:52.739
Sung-hun's first Paradise trip.

598
00:33:53.698 --> 00:33:55.867
-I wonder what his age and job are.
-Just who is he?

599
00:33:55.950 --> 00:33:57.744
Same. I wonder what his job is.

600
00:33:58.786 --> 00:34:00.371
After talking with him.

601
00:34:01.664 --> 00:34:03.666
we had more in common than I expected.

602
00:34:04.500 --> 00:34:07.670
I feel more comfortable with him
now that we've talked.

603
00:34:09.797 --> 00:34:14.135
He's someone who can really understand me.

604
00:34:19.474 --> 00:34:23.478
I think he's more proactive
when it's one-on-one.

605
00:34:23.561 --> 00:34:27.190
But here. in a group environment.
I think it's hard for him.

606
00:34:27.273 --> 00:34:28.983
-I see.
-For Sung-hun.

607
00:34:29.484 --> 00:34:31.444
-That's understandable.
-Right.

608
00:34:31.986 --> 00:34:33.154
I find it hard too.

609
00:34:35.907 --> 00:34:37.909
He seems like he'd be very sweet.

610
00:34:38.409 --> 00:34:40.119
-He seems like a sweet guy.
-Yes.

611
00:34:40.703 --> 00:34:41.621
He's very caring.

612
00:34:41.704 --> 00:34:42.789
-He's funny too.
-Right.

613
00:34:42.872 --> 00:34:44.957
-He's so fun.
-His reactions are so funny.

614
00:34:46.626 --> 00:34:47.794
He always says. "Damn."

615
00:34:52.048 --> 00:34:54.926
His pronunciation is great.
It makes it funnier. "Holy…"

616
00:34:59.222 --> 00:35:01.516
-Gosh. Mina Sue.
-I can't take this.

617
00:35:01.599 --> 00:35:04.727
Before. it was Hee-sun looking anxious
whenever Mina Sue talked.

618
00:35:04.811 --> 00:35:06.646
-Right.
-But now the tables have turned.

619
00:35:06.729 --> 00:35:08.898
-They've turned.
-Yes. they have.

620
00:35:09.941 --> 00:35:11.859
-Was it okay for you?
-Yes. I had fun.

621
00:35:11.943 --> 00:35:14.403
-It was fun? Tell me more.
-More?

622
00:35:15.488 --> 00:35:17.949
I honestly didn't expect
to have this much fun.

623
00:35:18.533 --> 00:35:19.951
-Really?
-Did you guys click?

624
00:35:20.034 --> 00:35:21.494
Yes. Really.

625
00:35:21.577 --> 00:35:23.204
As potential romantic partners?

626
00:35:23.788 --> 00:35:28.501
For starters. our values and dating styles
are exactly the same.

627
00:35:28.584 --> 00:35:30.461
We think the same way.

628
00:35:30.545 --> 00:35:32.755
-Really?
-It felt like looking in a mirror.

629
00:35:32.839 --> 00:35:35.716
We were both like.
"Wow. you're like this. too?"

630
00:35:35.800 --> 00:35:37.385
And it kept going like that.

631
00:35:37.969 --> 00:35:40.346
We were surprising each other
the whole time.

632
00:35:40.429 --> 00:35:41.931
So it was a lot of fun.

633
00:35:42.014 --> 00:35:45.017
-You really don't know them until you go.
-I think so.

634
00:35:45.101 --> 00:35:47.728
But I don't think

635
00:35:47.812 --> 00:35:52.567
it would've been to this extent
if I'd gone with someone else.

636
00:35:52.650 --> 00:35:54.902
-Really?
-Yes.

637
00:35:54.986 --> 00:35:57.697
It was fun because we were so alike.

638
00:35:57.780 --> 00:35:58.906
-I see.
-Yes.

639
00:36:05.663 --> 00:36:08.666
-Didn't Mina Sue look like that earlier?
-Yes. she looks anxious.

640
00:36:08.749 --> 00:36:09.917
-How funny.
-They're the same.

641
00:36:10.001 --> 00:36:10.835
This is fun.

642
00:36:10.918 --> 00:36:15.381
The main difference
after this trip to Paradise is that

643
00:36:15.464 --> 00:36:18.426
-it lit a fire in Mina Sue's belly…
-Yes.

644
00:36:18.509 --> 00:36:19.969
…namely her feelings for Sung-hun.

645
00:36:20.052 --> 00:36:21.846
I think that's changed.

646
00:36:21.929 --> 00:36:24.390
Mina Sue will experience
some heartache now. too.

647
00:36:26.017 --> 00:36:27.018
That scared me.

648
00:36:27.685 --> 00:36:29.020
I hate this so much.

649
00:36:29.103 --> 00:36:29.937
Please stop.

650
00:36:30.021 --> 00:36:34.692
<i>Today. the men will be competing in a game</i>
<i>for a date in Paradise.</i>

651
00:36:39.488 --> 00:36:40.406
It's a men's game.

652
00:36:40.489 --> 00:36:42.074
Here we go.

653
00:36:42.158 --> 00:36:44.869
-I want them to go head-to-head.
-You keep saying that.

654
00:36:45.953 --> 00:36:47.205
Just once.

655
00:36:47.705 --> 00:36:50.708
-I'd like to see them fight it out.
-Head-to-head?

656
00:36:51.626 --> 00:36:54.170
<i>Everyone. please gather</i>
<i>at the challenge area.</i>

657
00:36:55.046 --> 00:36:57.840
-The time has come.
-Let's make sure no one gets hurt.

658
00:37:00.843 --> 00:37:02.637
I'm honestly scared of I-geon today.

659
00:37:02.720 --> 00:37:04.263
-Today. I-geon is…
-Right.

660
00:37:04.347 --> 00:37:06.182
-He'll be so determined.
-I hope so.

661
00:37:21.489 --> 00:37:22.406
What's that line?

662
00:37:24.158 --> 00:37:25.409
-There's a line.
-Who will win?

663
00:37:28.704 --> 00:37:31.832
-I-geon put his hair down today.
-It looks better.

664
00:37:31.916 --> 00:37:33.000
-Right?
-Yes.

665
00:37:33.626 --> 00:37:37.171
-There's something in the middle.
-Is it a long jump competition?

666
00:37:43.344 --> 00:37:47.556
{\an8}<i>Today. the men will play a game</i>
<i>to win a date in Paradise.</i>

667
00:37:48.683 --> 00:37:52.770
{\an8}<i>Only the top three winners</i>
<i>in order of their ranking</i>

668
00:37:52.853 --> 00:37:57.233
{\an8}<i>can each pick a woman</i>
<i>to take on a date to Paradise.</i>

669
00:37:57.775 --> 00:37:58.943
Geez.

670
00:37:59.026 --> 00:38:01.529
<i>Here is today's game.</i>

671
00:38:02.071 --> 00:38:04.448
<i>Please open the box next to you.</i>

672
00:38:05.491 --> 00:38:06.325
What is it?

673
00:38:07.243 --> 00:38:08.077
What is this?

674
00:38:08.828 --> 00:38:10.079
-A rope?
-It's not a ball.

675
00:38:12.832 --> 00:38:14.458
Tug of war?

676
00:38:15.167 --> 00:38:18.212
<i>Today's game is Trench Tug of War.</i>

677
00:38:18.296 --> 00:38:20.589
Will they try to pull the other person
into the water?

678
00:38:20.673 --> 00:38:24.885
{\an8}<i>The men will wear shoulder bands</i>
<i>connected to a rope</i>

679
00:38:24.969 --> 00:38:28.431
{\an8}<i>and stand at the starting line</i>
<i>on opposite ends of the trench.</i>

680
00:38:29.223 --> 00:38:31.392
{\an8}<i>At the whistle. they will pull the rope.</i>

681
00:38:31.976 --> 00:38:35.396
{\an8}<i>The first to pull their opponent</i>
<i>into the trench wins.</i>

682
00:38:36.814 --> 00:38:39.817
{\an8}<i>If no winner is decided after one minute.</i>

683
00:38:40.443 --> 00:38:44.864
{\an8}<i>whoever is farther from the water</i>
<i>at that moment wins.</i>

684
00:38:45.906 --> 00:38:49.118
<i>It will be a tournament-style game.</i>

685
00:38:49.201 --> 00:38:52.121
If one moves forward.
the other person will fall.

686
00:38:52.204 --> 00:38:53.706
That's the game.

687
00:38:54.665 --> 00:38:55.916
That's insane.

688
00:38:56.876 --> 00:38:59.128
There was a similar game.
but without water.

689
00:38:59.211 --> 00:39:00.046
-Right.
-Right.

690
00:39:00.129 --> 00:39:03.424
-They'll fall into the water if they lose.
-They'll fly backwards.

691
00:39:03.507 --> 00:39:05.343
-With a flop. they'll get soaked.
-Splash.

692
00:39:06.010 --> 00:39:07.219
It's the worst.

693
00:39:07.303 --> 00:39:09.638
-especially in front of someone you like.
-Really.

694
00:39:09.722 --> 00:39:10.723
-Gosh.
-That's harsh.

695
00:39:10.806 --> 00:39:13.351
This is the last trip to Paradise.

696
00:39:13.434 --> 00:39:14.643
-Right.
-It's big.

697
00:39:14.727 --> 00:39:16.645
-They must give it their all.
-It'll be intense.

698
00:39:16.729 --> 00:39:17.563
Yes.

699
00:39:17.646 --> 00:39:19.315
-Sung-min has to show them.
-Yes.

700
00:39:19.398 --> 00:39:21.650
He should show them his manliness.

701
00:39:21.734 --> 00:39:26.155
Go-eun refers to Sung-min
as "Mr. Paper Doll." right?

702
00:39:26.238 --> 00:39:28.699
-Yes.
-It'd be nice if he showed her he's not.

703
00:39:28.783 --> 00:39:31.202
-Go-eun calls Sung-min Mr. Paper Doll.
-She does.

704
00:39:31.285 --> 00:39:32.912
-That's right. She does.
-Yes.

705
00:39:32.995 --> 00:39:34.997
-That hurt Sung-min's pride.
-Yes.

706
00:39:35.081 --> 00:39:37.208
That's why he said.
"I can lift that much."

707
00:39:37.291 --> 00:39:38.709
-"I step up when needed."
-Right.

708
00:39:38.793 --> 00:39:40.836
-Today is the day he gets to show her.
-Yes.

709
00:39:41.545 --> 00:39:44.882
I'd love to see Sung-min and I-geon
compete against each other.

710
00:39:44.965 --> 00:39:46.509
-That'd be fun.
-That'd be fun.

711
00:39:46.592 --> 00:39:47.927
Please be Sung-min versus I-geon.

712
00:39:48.010 --> 00:39:49.512
-Please!
-Sung-min and I-geon!

713
00:39:50.137 --> 00:39:53.224
<i>The matchups will be decided</i>
<i>by drawing balls.</i>

714
00:39:57.395 --> 00:39:59.021
<i>Jo I-geon picked a yellow ball.</i>

715
00:40:00.398 --> 00:40:02.066
I hate these darn balls.

716
00:40:02.691 --> 00:40:04.110
I really don't want to pick.

717
00:40:04.193 --> 00:40:05.027
Why not?

718
00:40:05.611 --> 00:40:07.405
<i>Lee Sung-hun picked a blue ball.</i>

719
00:40:10.157 --> 00:40:12.326
<i>Woo Sung-min picked a white ball.</i>

720
00:40:14.161 --> 00:40:15.830
They might match up in the next round.

721
00:40:15.913 --> 00:40:17.373
-True.
-It's a tournament.

722
00:40:17.998 --> 00:40:20.167
-All the colors are different.
-Right?

723
00:40:21.877 --> 00:40:23.671
<i>Youn Hyun-jae picked a blue ball.</i>

724
00:40:24.171 --> 00:40:25.673
{\an8}It's Sung-hun versus Hyun-jae.

725
00:40:25.756 --> 00:40:27.883
{\an8}BLUE BALL
LEE SUNG-HUN VS YOUN HYUN-JAE

726
00:40:27.967 --> 00:40:29.176
{\an8}They're close friends.

727
00:40:31.804 --> 00:40:33.597
{\an8}<i>Lim Su-been picked a yellow ball.</i>

728
00:40:33.681 --> 00:40:34.515
{\an8}It's I-geon.

729
00:40:34.598 --> 00:40:36.225
{\an8}YELLOW BALL
JO I-GEON VS YOUN HYUN-JAE

730
00:40:40.062 --> 00:40:42.189
{\an8}<i>Kim Jae-jin picked a white ball.</i>

731
00:40:42.773 --> 00:40:46.527
{\an8}WHITE BALL
WOO SUNG-MIN VS KIM JAE-JIN

732
00:40:46.610 --> 00:40:48.195
Sung-min might have a chance.

733
00:40:48.279 --> 00:40:50.030
-He's pretty lucky.
-He is.

734
00:40:50.114 --> 00:40:51.699
-Battle of the paper dolls.
-Seems fair.

735
00:40:52.199 --> 00:40:53.451
Every matchup seems fair.

736
00:40:53.534 --> 00:40:56.078
-"Battle of the paper dolls."
-Team Paper Dolls.

737
00:40:56.162 --> 00:41:00.458
-Good luck.
-That means it's Hyeon-woo and Seung-il.

738
00:41:02.960 --> 00:41:04.670
That's a big match.

739
00:41:05.254 --> 00:41:07.089
We should've met at the final match.

740
